<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 04 at 1:57PM CDT until April 04 at 2:15PM CDT by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 215 PM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN PONTOTOC...SOUTHWESTERN POTTAWATOMIE AND
SOUTHEASTERN MCCLAIN COUNTIES...
At 156 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Asher, moving
east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Asher, Wanette, Byars and St. Louis.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
